    <!-- Section 1: Overview -->
    <section id="overview" class="doc-section mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
            <div class="section-number">1</div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold" style="color: var(--doc-text);">State Management Overview</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="rounded-xl p-6 border" style="background: var(--doc-card-bg); border-color: var(--doc-border);">
            <p class="mb-4" style="color: var(--doc-text);">
                The Dawn Framework provides a dual-state architecture that separates <strong>server-side state</strong> (shared across all clients) 
                from <strong>client-side state</strong> (isolated per client). This approach enables:
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
                <div class="feature-card p-4">
                    <h3 class="font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--doc-text);">📦 Server State</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--doc-text-secondary);">Shared across all connected clients. Persisted to Redis automatically. Perfect for application data.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card p-4">
                    <h3 class="font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--doc-text);">🖥️ Client State</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--doc-text-secondary);">Isolated per client session. Persisted to Redis with client identifier. Perfect for UI state and forms.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card p-4">
                    <h3 class="font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--doc-text);">💾 Redis Persistence</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--doc-text-secondary);">Automatic persistence with TTL. Supports reconnection and state recovery.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-box">
                <strong>💡 Key Insight:</strong> Server state is updated via <code>setState()</code> and affects all users. Client state is updated via <code>setClientState()</code> and is unique per user session.
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: Understanding State Types -->
    <section id="state-types" class="doc-section mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
            <div class="section-number">2</div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold" style="color: var(--doc-text);">Understanding State Types</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="rounded-xl p-6 border" style="background: var(--doc-card-bg); border-color: var(--doc-border);">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--doc-text);">State Comparison</h3>
            
            <table class="comparison-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Server State</th><th>Client State</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Scope</td><td>All connected clients</td><td>Single client session</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Update Method</td><td><code>setState()</code></td><td><code>setClientState()</code></td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Redis Key Pattern</td><td><code>component_state:key</code></td><td><code>client_state:key:client_token</code></td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Use Cases</td><td>Application data, shared resources</td><td>Form inputs, UI preferences, temporary data</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Persistence</td><td>Global with component key</td><td>Per client with token</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            
            <div class="method-signature">
                <strong>State Structure:</strong> Both state types are Lua tables that can contain nested data structures.
            </div>
            
            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="code-header">
                    <span class="code-language"><i class="fab fa-lua"></i> Lua - State Structures</span>
                    <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)"><i class="fas fa-copy"></i> Copy</button>
                </div>
                <pre><code><span class="comment">-- Example State Structures</span>
<span class="keyword">local</span> serverState = {
    tasks = {
        { id = <span class="number">1</span>, title = <span class="string">"Task 1"</span>, completed = <span class="keyword">false</span> },
        { id = <span class="number">2</span>, title = <span class="string">"Task 2"</span>, completed = <span class="keyword">true</span> }
    },
    nextId = <span class="number">3</span>,
    settings = {
        theme = <span class="string">"dark"</span>,
        notifications = <span class="keyword">true</span>
    }
}

<span class="comment">-- Example Client State (isolated per user)</span>
<span class="keyword">local</span> clientState = {
    draftForm = {
        name = <span class="string">""</span>,
        email = <span class="string">""</span>
    },
    uiPreferences = {
        sidebarCollapsed = <span class="keyword">false</span>,
        activeTab = <span class="string">"tasks"</span>
    },
    temporaryData = {
        searchQuery = <span class="string">""</span>
    }
}</code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: Server State -->
    <section id="server-state" class="doc-section mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
            <div class="section-number">3</div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold" style="color: var(--doc-text);">Server State (Component State)</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="rounded-xl p-6 border" style="background: var(--doc-card-bg); border-color: var(--doc-border);">
            <p class="mb-4" style="color: var(--doc-text);">
                Server state is stored in the <code>self.state</code> table of your component. Updates to this state affect all connected clients 
                and are automatically persisted to Redis when available.
            </p>
            
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3" style="color: var(--doc-text);">Setting Up Server State</h3>
            
            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="code-header">
                    <span class="code-language"><i class="fab fa-lua"></i> Lua - Server State Setup</span>
                    <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)"><i class="fas fa-copy"></i> Copy</button>
                </div>
                <pre><code><span class="comment">-- Initialize component with server state</span>
<span class="keyword">local</span> MyComponent = FunctionalComponent:extends()
MyComponent:setReactiveView()

<span class="comment">-- Define initial state (optional, will be loaded from Redis if available)</span>
MyComponent.state = {
    items = {},
    nextId = <span class="number">1</span>,
    settings = {
        maxItems = <span class="number">100</span>
    }
}

<span class="comment">-- Load state from Redis (called after setComponentKey)</span>
MyComponent:loadStateFromRedis()</code></pre>
            </div>
            
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3" style="color: var(--doc-text);">Updating Server State</h3>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div class="method-card">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2" style="color: var(--doc-text);">Method 1: Partial Table Update</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--doc-text-secondary);">Merge changes into existing state.</p>
                    <div class="code-block" style="margin: 0;">
                        <pre><code>MyComponent:setState({
    items = { { id = <span class="number">1</span>, title = <span class="string">"New Task"</span> } }
})</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="method-card">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2" style="color: var(--doc-text);">Method 2: Updater Function</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm mb-3" style="color: var(--doc-text-secondary);">Calculate new state based on current.</p>
                    <div class="code-block" style="margin: 0;">
                        <pre><code>MyComponent:setState(<span class="keyword">function</span>(currentState)
    <span class="keyword">local</span> newItem = {
        id = currentState.nextId,
        title = <span class="string">"New Item"</span>
    }
    <span class="keyword">return</span> {
        items = { table.unpack(currentState.items), newItem },
        nextId = currentState.nextId + <span class="number">1</span>
    }
<span class="keyword">end</span>)</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="warning-box mt-4">
                <strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Server state updates trigger re-renders for ALL connected clients. Use sparingly for high-frequency updates or consider client state for user-specific data.
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Client State -->
    <section id="client-state" class="doc-section mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
            <div class="section-number">4</div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold" style="color: var(--doc-text);">Client State</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="rounded-xl p-6 border" style="background: var(--doc-card-bg); border-color: var(--doc-border);">
            <p class="mb-4" style="color: var(--doc-text);">
                Client state is isolated per user session and stored with a client token or WebSocket ID. Perfect for UI state, form drafts, 
                and user preferences that shouldn't affect other users.
            </p>
            
            <div class="code-block">
                <div class="code-header">
                    <span class="code-language"><i class="fab fa-lua"></i> Lua - Client State Setup</span>
                    <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)"><i class="fas fa-copy"></i> Copy</button>
                </div>
                <pre><code>MyComponent:onClientReady(<span class="keyword">function</span>(self, ws_id, client_token)
    <span class="comment">-- Initialize client state for this user</span>
    self:setClientState(ws_id, {
        tasks = {},
        nextClientId = <span class="number">1</span>,
        uiState = {
            sidebarOpen = <span class="keyword">true</span>,
            activeTab = <span class="string">"all"</span>
        }
    }, <span class="string">"my_component"</span>)
<span class="keyword">end</span>)</code></pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="info-box mt-4">
                <strong>💡 Tip:</strong> Client state is automatically persisted to Redis with the pattern <code>client_state:{component_key}:{client_token}</code>. 
                When a user reconnects, their state is restored automatically.
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 5: Redis Persistence -->
